    <body>
      <head>Hedda (Hedl) Glässner [Delmonte]</head>
      <div>

        <p>Daughter of <ref cRef="entity-008846">Theodor Glässner</ref> and <ref
            cRef="entity-003425">Frieda (<hi rend="italic">née</hi> Schiff)</ref>, thus niece of
            <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker (<hi rend="italic">née</hi> Schiff)</ref>;
          mother of Heinz Georg and Gert.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>Hedda married <ref cRef="entity-003921">Hans Delmonte</ref> of the Hamburg Delmonte
          banking house; <ref cRef="entity-000781">Anna Schiff</ref> reported that “her
          mother[-in-law] enabled her to build a villa” (<ref type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-14-8_1"
            >OJ 14/8, [1]</ref>, March 23, 1925). She and Hans initially lived in <ref
            cRef="entity-002589">Hamburg</ref>, where their two children, Heinz Georg (1923–1997),
          and Gert (1925–), were born. By 1935 they were living in <ref cRef="entity-002501"
            >Berlin</ref> (Wilmersdorf, Landauerstraße 3), but by April 1938 the family was living
          in Lisbon, from where they emigrated to <ref cRef="entity-006588">Brazil</ref>, settling
          in Rio de Janeiro.</p>
      </div>

